HEADWORD: Pleuroderes
<hw>Pleu*rod"e*res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ the side + <?/ the neck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
group of fresh-water turtles in which the neck can not be retracted, but
is bent to one side, for protection. The <stype>matamata</stype> is an
example.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

